## Post 5

**Date:** 30 June 2026

**Topic:** Optimizing YouTube for B2B growth

### Summary
Ross argues that many B2B companies treat YouTube as a repository for webinars and podcasts instead of managing it as a strategic content platform. He explains how optimizing thumbnails, titles, descriptions, playlists, and publishing consistency significantly improved video performance for one client. He also notes that optimized YouTube videos are increasingly cited by AI systems and perform well in Google Search.

### Main Takeaway
Treat YouTube like a strategic content platform—not a video archive—to improve discoverability, AI visibility, and business results.

